ROCKNIX ABL for SM8250 — YOU PROBABLY DO NOT NEED THIS. The Retroid Pocket 5's
STOCK ABL boots this SD directly (it chainloads EFI/BOOT/bootaa64.efi; verified
on hardware 2026-07 — the same way stock boots ROCKNIX SDs), and the ROCKNIX ABL
is known to be flaky on SM8250, so most users avoid flashing it there. This
folder is kept for parity with ROCKNIX's SD layout and for boards/situations
where the stock ABL cannot SD-boot. If you truly need it (one-time flash from
the Android side; scripts verbatim from ROCKNIX's rocknix-abl package,
flash_abl.sh templated for SM8250):

- Copy the rocknix_abl folder from the SD card to the root of Android Internal Storage
- Execute as root the backup_abl.sh script from the Internal Storage to backup your current ABL
- After backup, execute as root the flash_abl.sh script to flash the new ABL
- Reboot your device holding Vol - key to enter fastboot menu
- Select "Change boot mode" option using Vol -/+ key, and hit Power button
- Hit Power button to start
